<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.182765>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Ventral view of lower lip morphology in: (A) Sinocrossocheilus guizhouensis, IHB 6650508, lectotype, 59.0 mm SL; (B) Sinocrossocheilus labiatus; KIZ 995338, holotype, 56.1 mm SL; (C) Hongshuia paoli, IHB 200210911, holotype, 54.3 mm SL; (D) Hongshuia microstomatus, IHB 87 IV 506, paratype, 81.7 mm SL; (E) Pseudocrossocheilus bamaensis, IHB 85 VII 056, 152.9 mm SL; (F) Pseudocrossocheilus tridentis, KIZ 774079, holotype, 118.0 mm SL. cf = crescentic fold of median lobe of lower lip; fp = fleshy pad of median lobe of lower lip; mb = median lobe of lower lip; rlf = ring-like fold of median lobe of lower lip." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/182765/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

